The players understand what this means: relegation would be a disaster for the club and for our supporters. They're determined to make sure it doesn't happen. We have to win.

We've got what we deserved.
At the end of the season, the table doesn't lie. It's not just what happened here. It's all the points we dropped and the chances we missed that brought us to this dark day for the club.
